		<t>
            <field>CDUniqueIdentifier</field>
            <desc>
                <p>Unique Identifier is a global unique number for each processed item. </p>
				<p>It needs to be stored in the cheque imaging system, outward clearing data file, outward index file, inward clearing data file and inward index file. </p>
				<p>It can be used as the unique search key for item search and return cheque process.</p>
				<p>Format of UID: YYYYMMDDBBBCNNNNNNNNNN</p>
				<p>where:</p>
				<p>YYYYMMDD = Clearing Date</p>
				<p>BBB = Collecting Member Clearing Code (i.e. 307)</p>
				<p>C = Capture Point (0=HKCLG, 1=Group A Member)</p>
				<p>NNNNNNNNNN = 10 digits Sequence Number</p>
                <p>Validation Rules:</p>
                <p>22 alphanumeric characters</p>
            </desc>
        </t>			
